      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Competitive. HASANI (1) resumed for the new yard with an even effort over this trip at Ascot in an Open 3. He'd come off a go at Group 2 level and is proven second-up. Has a handy gate and a 2kg claim, and the colt has plenty up his sleeve. SO MUCH SERENITY (10) brought strong form to Ascot third-up and disappointed over this distance as a $2.7 favourite (vet cleared). She's been given 28 days away and can get back on track. Pike gets off, but she certainly deserves another chance. JOYOH (8) resumed further improved with a Maiden win at Belmont. Didn't have the best of it against the above following, but finally draws a low gate, and Pike is a key jockey switch. Will strip fitter and is likely to feature. GOLDEN CHATTER (2) and LE FEM LE CHOIX (9) both present off metro Maiden wins. They have plenty of scope for improvement and look well in the mix.",
